Three people were killed and three others wounded in three separate attacks by militants in Afghanistan on Monday, authorities said. In eastern Ghazni province, the attackers opened fire on two provincial revenue directorate workers and killed them in Police District 2 of the provincial capital Ghazni city at about 8 a.m. local time. Ahmad Khan Sirat, provincial police spokesman, told Xinhua that the customs workers were on their way to the office and were killed by “terrorists” equipped with silencer weapons. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! In neighbouring Khost province, an improvised bomb targeted the vehicle of Sayyed Asghar Akakhil, a provincial council member, on the outskirts of the provincial capital Khost city. The attack killed one security guard, wounded Akakhil and a security guard, the chairman of the council, Rahis Kafel Rayhan, told Xinhua. COVID-19: Japan Bans Travelers From 152 Countries India Inaugurates First-Ever Driverless Metro Train Earlier on Monday, a driver of the Ministry of Defence was wounded after an improvised bomb hit a ministry’s vehicle in Police District 4 of the national capital Kabul, police said. No group has so far claimed responsibility for the attacks. Last week, Yousuf Rashid, chairman of Free and Fair Election Forum of Afghanistan, an independent election monitoring agency, was killed, while a female activist and her brother were also killed. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION